      "**Step 5: Download** — Click the download button next to your chosen MP3 quality. The file will be saved to your device ready for playback.",
      "## Understanding MP3 Quality (Bitrate)",
      "MP3 quality is measured in kilobits per second (kbps). Higher bitrates mean better audio quality but larger file sizes. Here's a breakdown of what each bitrate level offers and when to use it:",
      "**64 kbps:** Very low quality. Noticeable compression artifacts, tinny sound. Only suitable for speech content where clarity isn't critical. File size: ~0.5 MB per minute.",
      "**128 kbps:** Acceptable quality for casual listening. Most people won't notice issues with speech content, but music may sound slightly compressed. This is the standard quality for many streaming services on mobile. File size: ~1 MB per minute.",
      "**192 kbps:** Good quality. Suitable for most music and speech content. The sweet spot between file size and quality for everyday listening. File size: ~1.5 MB per minute.",
      "**256 kbps:** Very good quality. Hard to distinguish from the original for most listeners, even with good headphones. File size: ~2 MB per minute.",
